    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Musical compositions that are free in form and inspiration, usually for an instrumental soloist. Examples include 16th- and 17th-century English fugal compositions (i.e., based on melodic imitation) for consorts of string or wind instruments, and earlier 16th-century works for lute or keyboard consisting of short sections based on one or more musical motives.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
